@{
    ViewBag.Title = "SaaS.NET";
}

<div class="row" style="border:solid thin black; background-color:aliceblue;">
    <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-push-6" style="text-align:center;">
        <img src="http://equations.ae/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/saas.png" />
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-pull-6">
        <div class="text-center">
            <h1>SaaS.NET</h1>
        </div>
        <p class="lead">SaaS.NET provides the perfect starting point for your next big idea. Forget all the boilerplate and focus on what matters: <b>your ASP.NET MVC 5 application</b>.</p>
        
        <div class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1">
            <p><a href="http://asp.net" class="btn btn-primary form-control">Learn more about SaaS.NET &raquo;</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>    
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Authentication</h2>
        <p>Authentication, registration, and password reset are ready out of the box. It’s never been faster to get started building your dreams.</p>
        @Html.ActionLink("Learn more \u00BB", "Index", "Docs", "", new { @class = "btn btn-default" })
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Subscriptions</h2>
        <p>Subscription billing without the hassle. Offer monthly and yearly plans with Stripe or Braintree. Define plans using expressive code and get started building what matters: your business.</p>
        @Html.ActionLink("Learn more \u00BB", "Index", "Docs", "", new { @class = "btn btn-default" })
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Teams</h2>
        <p>Allow your users to create, join, and invite other users to their teams without writing a single line of code. Spending weeks of writing boilerplate is so last year.</p>
        @Html.ActionLink("Learn more \u00BB", "Index", "Docs", "", new { @class = "btn btn-default" })
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Invoices</h2>
        <p>Allow your customers to download PDF copies of their invoices. SaaS.NET will even automatically e-mail your customers their monthly invoice. One more thing you don’t have to worry about.</p>
        @Html.ActionLink("Learn more \u00BB", "Index", "Docs", "", new { @class = "btn btn-default" })
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Team Billing</h2>
        <p>Allow each team to have its own billing plan. Think of it like GitHub Organizations. All without writing a single line of code. Tears of joy are nothing to be ashamed of.</p>
        @Html.ActionLink("Learn more \u00BB", "Index", "Docs", "", new { @class = "btn btn-default" })
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Announcements</h2>
        <p>Make announcements to your customers so they are always in the loop. SaaS.NET makes it a cinch to always keep in touch with your customers.</p>
        @Html.ActionLink("Learn more \u00BB", "Index", "Docs", "", new { @class = "btn btn-default" })
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>User Impersonation</h2>
        <p>Debugging a problem and need to login as one of your customers? SaaS.NET’s developer Kiosk allows you to authenticate as any of your customers.</p>
        @Html.ActionLink("Learn more \u00BB", "Index", "Docs", "", new { @class = "btn btn-default" })
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Two-Factor Authentication</h2>
        <p>Want to offer two-factor authentication to your customers? SaaS.NET has you covered with just a few lines of code. Use Authy or your own two-factor authentication provider.</p>
        @Html.ActionLink("Learn more \u00BB", "Index", "Docs", "", new { @class = "btn btn-default" })
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>API Out Of The Box</h2>
        <p>SaaS.NET allows your customers to generate API tokens and even grant specific abilities to tokens. Of course, API authentication is ready out of the box. Share your API with your JavaScript client and your SDKs.</p>
        @Html.ActionLink("Learn more \u00BB", "Index", "Docs", "", new { @class = "btn btn-default" })
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Customizable</h2>
        <p>Need to customize a piece of SaaS.NET? No problem. Replace small pieces or entire chunks of SaaS.NET with just a few lines of code. You can even extend SaaS.NET’s JavaScript. Tailor SaaS.NET to your needs or stick with the defaults - it’s up to you!</p>
        @Html.ActionLink("Learn more \u00BB", "Index", "Docs", "", new { @class = "btn btn-default" })
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Free</h2>
        <p>SaaS.NET is free to use! Save hours of development time with this simple solution.</p>
        @Html.ActionLink("Learn more \u00BB", "Index", "Docs", "", new { @class = "btn btn-default" })
    </div>
</div>